display.label: Encrypt Message
display.description: Encrypt a string message with a password or PGP public key

inputs.comments: Provide a string password to encrypt the message. You can elect to encrypt the message with a password or public PGP key, but not both.
inputs.label: Password

inputs.comments: Provide a string PGP public key to encrypt the message. You can elect to encrypt the message with a password or public PGP key, but not both.
inputs.example:
-----BEGIN PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----
EXAMPLE==
-----END PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----
inputs.label: Public Key

display.label: Decrypt Message
display.description: Decrypt a string message with a password or PGP private key and passphrase

inputs.comments: Provide a string password to encrypt the message. You can elect to encrypt the message with a password or public PGP key, but not both.
inputs.label: Password

inputs.comments: Provide a string PGP pviate key to decrypt the message. You can elect to decrypt the message with a password or private PGP key, but not both.
inputs.example:
-----BEGIN PGP PRIVATE KEY BLOCK-----
EXAMPLE==
-----END PGP PRIVATE KEY BLOCK-----
inputs.label: Private Key

inputs.comments: Provide a string passphrase for your private key if you are using a private key to decrypt the message
inputs.label: Private Key Passphrase

documentation.description:
[Pretty Good Privacy](https://project.microsoft.com/en-US/) is an encryption program that provides cryptographic privacy and authentication for data communication.
This component allows you to encrypt and decrypt strings in an integration.
documentation.dev:
You can elect to encrypt or decrypt strings using either a password or a public/private key pair.
RSA key pairs of any key size are compatible with these actions.
